No. 30,

Original.

Michigan v. Ohio. Frank J. Kelley, Attorney General of Michigan, Robert A. DerengosUi, Solicitor General, and Nicholas V. Olds and Esther E. Newton, Assistant Attorneys General, on the ■ motion. William B. Saxbe, Attorney General of Ohio, and Charles S. Lopeman for defendant in opposition.'

Motion for leave to file a bill of complaint granted and State of Ohio allowed sixty days to answer.
